-- Davids Joins English Fourth-Tier Club Barnet as Player-Coach
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-10-12T07:09:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-12/davids-joins-english-fourth-tier-club-barnet-as-player-coach.html
Former Netherlands midfielder Edgar Davids joined English fourth-tier soccer club Barnet as joint
head coach and will also seek to resume his playing career, the
team said.  Davids, who’s played for clubs including Ajax, AC Milan,
Juventus and Tottenham Hotspur, will become joint head coach
alongside Mark Robson at the club, Barnet said in a statement on
its website. Davids, 39, also intends to play for the team that
currently occupies last place among  England ’s four professional
soccer leagues.  “The capture of Davids is a statement of intent by our
club to improve results and lay further foundations for the
future,” Paul Fairclough, the club’s director of football, said
in the statement. “Edgar is a world-renowned footballer and
will be a great example to all our young players.”  Davids, who played 74 times for the Netherlands national
team, has been out of soccer since a brief stint with London
club Crystal Palace in 2010. He first retired as a player when
his second stint at Ajax ended in 2008.  Davids won one Champions League title, one UEFA Cup and
three national championships in  Italy  and the Netherlands. He
first retired from football when his second stint at Ajax ended
in 2008.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
